name: mapreduce.jobhistory.loadedjobs.cache.size
description:
Size of the loaded job cache.  This property is ignored if
  the property mapreduce.jobhistory.loadedtasks.cache.size is set to a
  positive value.

name: dfs.qjournal.accept-recovery.timeout.ms
description:
Quorum timeout in milliseconds during accept phase of
    recovery/synchronization for a specific segment.

name: dfs.datanode.max.slowdisks.to.exclude
description:
The number of slow disks that needs to be excluded. By default, this parameter is set to 0,
    which disables excluding slow disk when choosing volume.

name: mapreduce.jobhistory.datestring.cache.size
description:
Size of the date string cache. Effects the number of directories
  which will be scanned to find a job.

name: hadoop.fuse.connection.timeout
description:
The minimum number of seconds that we'll cache libhdfs connection objects
    in fuse_dfs. Lower values will result in lower memory consumption; higher
    values may speed up access by avoiding the overhead of creating new
    connection objects.

name: dfs.journalnode.edits.dir.perm
description:
Permissions for the directories on on the local filesystem where
      the DFS journal node stores the edits. The permissions can either be
      octal or symbolic.

name: dfs.provided.aliasmap.inmemory.batch-size
description: The batch size when iterating over the database backing the aliasmap
